content:
When you upload .csv data to create or update a dataset, you can select the time zone of the data if itâ€™s not GMT.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Also available in Developer Edition with CRM Analytics.

Upload your .CSV file to create a dataset.
Specify the source and target time zone at the page where you create a name and select an app for the dataset.
From the Source File Time Zone picklist, select the time zone of the data. The Target Time Zone is the time zone selected for your org in settings.

CRM Analytics converts date-time values in the file from the source time-zone to the target time zone in the resulting dataset.
title: Setting Source Time Zone for CSV Data Upload
